Defendant Julius J Williams in court with attorney Virginia Stuller for Glen B. Kulkoski.  Defendant Julius J Williams in custody.  Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for final pre-trial, however parties would like to proceed with a plea hearing instead.  Jury trial date of 01/06/2016 is vacated.  As to Counts 1 and 2:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
  Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 22.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 6, 2016 at 08:30 am.
